      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my blueberry bushes are starting to look kinda yellow on the leaves. is that usually a nitrogen thing or is the soil ph messing with it? i'm not sure what to check first.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing leaves on blueberry bushes can be caused by various issues, and it's tricky to tell if it's nitrogen deficiency or soil pH imbalance by just looking. Begin by checking the soil pH, as blueberries are very sensitive and thrive in acidic conditions, usually between 4.5 and 5.5. If the pH is too high, the plant can't properly absorb nutrients, even if they are present in the soil.",
      "source": "target",
