    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "oh okay so if the ph is a problem i should probably get a kit to test it. but how can i tell if it's specifically the ph vs just needing more fertilizer? is there a way to see if the nutrients are actually there but just stuck?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If you suspect the nutrients are \"stuck\" due to pH, a soil test is the most definitive way to check *both* the pH and the actual nutrient levels simultaneously. A simple pH kit gives you one number, but a comprehensive soil test tells you what the soil *has* versus what the plant *can use*. If the test shows adequate nitrogen but the pH is outside the ideal range, then the pH is the primary culprit preventing uptake.",
      "source": "target",
