    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "makes sense. i'll order a kit tonight. i'm also kinda worried about what's happening under the surface though. like, could there be something else going on in the dirt itself, like pests or something eating the roots that would make them look like they aren't getting food?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, root issues are a very common cause of nutrient deficiency symptoms, mimicking a lack of fertilizer. Inspect the base of the bushes and gently dig around a few plants to look for signs of root rot, which is often caused by overwatering. You might also see signs of pests like root aphids or nematodes, which can physically damage the roots and stop nutrient absorption.",
      "source": "target",
